Philadelphia Union (0-0-1) vs. CF Montreal (0-1-0)
Montreal, Quebec; Saturday, 4 p.m. EST
FANDUEL SPORTSBOOK
 LINE: Montreal +143, Philadelphia +194, Draw +226; over/under is 2.5 goals
BOTTOM LINE: The Philadelphia Union visit CF Montreal in Eastern Conference action.
Montreal finished 12-12-10 overall and 9-4-4 at home a season ago. Montreal scored 46 goals a season ago while allowing opponents to score 44.
The Union put together a 14-8-12 record overall in 2021 while finishing 3-5-9 in road games. The Union averaged 1.4 goals on 4.0 shots on goal per game a season ago.
The teams meet Saturday for the first time this season.
NOT EXPECTED TO PLAY: Montreal: Ahmed Hamdi (injured), Samuel Piette (injured), Mason Toye (injured).
Union: Quinn Sullivan (injured), Sergio Santos (injured), Joe Bendik (injured).
